snippet.textDisplay: I think ima pass on this one and wait to see what they do with next years phone. Don't get me wrong i think it's a great phone, but I don't get how they can have that big ass camera but no aux port. Also not a fan of how the power button and volume rockers are on the same side, I know that's a nit picky thing to not like but 🤷🏽‍♂️it just bothers me lmao. And they got rid of the bixby button which is a big L. I don't use it for bixby but I do use it to turn on my flash light, take screenshots, and change my phone from vibrate to sound and vice versa. Deadass the bixby button is one of the best things samsung added to their phones if you get an app to override bixby and pick what you want it to do. Again, this phone looks absolutely amazing but I think ima just keep my s10 until next year and see what they do then.

snippet.textDisplay:
This phone has wayyyyyyy too many specs.
Like are you supposed to get this for gaming? What games?
Watching videos on YouTube? You can't even get higher than 1080p on 99% of the content.
For shooting photos? Yeah might be a slightly better than competition but if you're a professional there are way more expensive equipment for professional shooting.
Downloading stuff in 5G? What do you need to download so much you need 5G connection?

You could just get the the Samsung A51 and it would have all the specs that are required for mostly everything. Yeah you cannot run Fortnite in 120hz but who plays on a phone anyway?
